title: iRobot Roomba 800 Series - How to Clean Front Caster Wheel
description: iRobot Roomba 800 Series - How to Clean Front Caster Wheel.

asset.author: iRobot
asset.hookText: iRobot Roomba 800 Series - How to Clean Front Caster Wheel.

transcripts: To clean Roomba's front caster wheel, pull firmly on the front wheel to remove it from the robot. Remove the debris from inside the front wheel cabinet. Remove the front wheel from it's housing by pushing it through from underneath. Clear any hair wrapped around the wear guard.  Then remove the axle from the wheel. Clear away any hair or debris from the axle and wheel assembly. Reinstall the wear guards and shaft assembly to the wheel and the wheel to the housing and the housing into the robot.
